1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new model for tensor completion using the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) and provides experimental results to demonstrate its effectiveness. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper analyzes the sample complexity of tensor completion using the tensor ring (TR) decomposition and proposes a nuclear norm minimization model. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a numerical method (ADMM) to solve the nuclear norm minimization model for tensor completion. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the representation ability of the tensor ring (TR) decomposition and its performance in tensor completion. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although not directly related to social networks, the paper's topic of tensor completion has applications in network analysis and could be of interest to researchers in this sub-category.
